# Mermaid Diagrams (Cursor-safe)

When adding or editing ` ```mermaid ` blocks in plans or docs, write diagrams that render in **Cursor Plan/Markdown preview** (Mermaid ~9–10). Prefer patterns already used in [sqlite audit plan](.cursor/plans/sqlite_请求审计日志_d28e8248.plan.md).

## Diagram type

- **Prefer `flowchart`** (`flowchart TB` / `flowchart LR`) for roadmaps and architecture.
- **Avoid `gantt` in `.cursor/plans/`** unless the user explicitly wants a dated timeline; Plan preview often fails on gantt (`title` quotes, task colons). Use a staged `flowchart LR` instead.

## Flowchart — do

- Subgraphs: `subgraph phase0 [Phase0_Contract]` — title in `[brackets]` **without** extra quotes: not `["Today"]`.
- Node labels with spaces or punctuation: `nodeId["Plain text label"]`.
- Edge labels: `A -.->|same DB different tables| B` (pipes, no nested `"` around label text).
- Cross-subgraph links: allowed; keep node ids unique (`memTarget`, not `target`).

## Flowchart — avoid

| Problem | Example | Use instead |
| -------- | -------- | ------------ |
| `+` in label | `["State + memory"]` | `["State with memory"]` or `and` |
| File paths in label | `["docs/foo.md"]` | `["foo doc"]` or `agent-memory doc` |
| Dotted extensions in label | `["App.tsx state"]` | `["App state"]` |
| Quoted subgraph title | `subgraph x ["Today"]` | `subgraph x [Today]` |
| Reserved-ish subgraph id | `subgraph target` | `subgraph memTarget` or `subgraph tgt` |

## Gantt (docs only, if required)

```mermaid
gantt
    dateFormat  YYYY-MM-DD
    title       Memory roadmap
    section Foundation
    Stage0 contract    :s0, 2026-06-01, 1d
    Stage1 wire fields :s1, after s0, 2d
```

- `title` **without** quotes.
- Task name, then space, then `:id,` metadata — every `after <id>` must reference a defined `:id`.
- No `#`, `;`, or `:` inside **section** names or task titles.

## Before saving

- Blank line before ` ```mermaid ` fence.
- No `---` horizontal rule immediately inside the code block.
- After edits, skim the block for `+`, `/`, quoted subgraph titles, and gantt in plan files.
